elements.name: Notification ID
elements.description: The unique identifier for the notification record.

hl7v251.messageContext: MSH-10-Message Control ID
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
If notification ID is not unique, a timestamp may be appended.  HL7 recommended size increased to 50.
 No UID or label is passed in the message.

elements.name: Receiving Application
elements.description: CDC Receiving Application for this message.

hl7v251.messageContext: MSH-5 Receiving Application

elements.name: Message Profile Identifier
elements.description:
First instance is the reference to the structural specification used to validate the message.
Second instance is the reference to the PHIN Message Mapping Guide from which the content is derived.

hl7v251.messageContext: MSH-21-Message Profile ID
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
First instance literal value: ‘NND_ORU_v2.0^PHINProfileID^2.16.840.1.114222.4.10.3^ISO'
Second instance literal value: ‘Arbo_Case_Map_v1.0^PHINMsgMapID^2.16.840.1.114222.4.10.4^ISO’.

elements.name: Patient name type
elements.description: Name is not requested by the program, but the Patient Name field is required to be populated for the HL7 message to be valid.  Have adopted the HL7 convention for processing a field where the name has been removed for de-identification purposes.

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-5 Patient Name field
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
Literal value:  |~^^^^^^S|

SECOND INSTANCE - where PID-5.7 Patient Name Type - is S for Pseudonym.  HL7 reserves the first instance of the name for Legal Name.

elements.name: Local Subject ID
elements.description: The local ID of the patient/entity.

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-3 Patient Identifier List
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
Only the sending system's internally assigned patient id used for these de-identified messages

where PID-3.1 ID Number is the local patient ID; 
PID-3.4 Assigning Authority format <localID&OID&ISO>
Does not pass Variable ID  or label.

elements.name: Birth Date
elements.description: Date of birth in YYYYMMDD format

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-7 Date/Time of Birth
hl7v251.implementationNotes: No UID or label is passed in the message.

elements.name: Subject’s Sex
elements.description: Patient’s current sex.

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-8 Administrative Sex
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
No UID or label is passed in the message.

DMB will fail the message if an invalid value is sent.

elements.name: Subject Address State
elements.description: State of residence of the subject.

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-11.4 Patient Address  - State

elements.name: Subject Address County
elements.description: County of residence of the subject.

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-11.9 Patient Address  - County
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
Use 5 character numeric code from PHVS_County_FIPS_6-4

DMB Will fail the message if data is not received in this field.

elements.name: Subject Address ZIP Code
elements.description: ZIP Code of residence of the subject.

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-11.5 Patient Address  - Postal Code

elements.name: Race Category
elements.description: Field containing one or more codes that broadly refer to the patient’s race(s).

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-10 Race

elements.name: Ethnic Group
elements.description: Ethnic origin or ethnicity is based on the individual’s self-identity of the patient as Hispanic or Latino; choose one value from the list.

hl7v251.messageContext: PID-22 Ethnic Group

elements.name: Subject Type
elements.description: Type of subject for the notification.  "Person", "Place/location", or "Non-Person Living Subject" are the appropriate subject types for Notifications to CDC.

hl7v251.messageContext: First OBR Segment-OBR-4-Universal Service ID
hl7v251.implementationNotes: Literal Value:  'PERSUBJ^Person Subject^CDCPHINVS'

elements.name: Notification Type
elements.description: Type of notification. Notification types are "Individual Case",  "Environmental", "Summary", and "Laboratory Report".

hl7v251.messageContext: Second OBR Segment-OBR-4-Universal Service ID
hl7v251.implementationNotes: Literal Value:  'NOTF^Individual Case Notification^CDCPHINVS'

elements.name: Country of Birth
elements.description: Country of Birth

hl7v251.messageContext: Observation/OBX Segment with this variable ID and label

elements.name: Country of Usual Residence
elements.description:
Where does the person usually live (defined as their residence).

This variable replaces the Foreign Resident variable mentioned in 11-SI-04 titled "Revised Guidelines for Determining Residency for Disease Reporting" located at http://c.ymcdn.com/sites/www.cste.org/resource/resmgr/PS/11-SI-04.pdf.

Cases with country of usual residence equal to the US, Puerto Rico, and US Virgin Islands as well as unknown and null responses will be included in the state-specific counts and rates.

hl7v251.messageContext: Observation/OBX Segment with this variable ID and label

elements.name: Condition Code
elements.description:
Condition or event that constitutes the reason the notification is being sent. 

Refer to the Event Code List of Nationally Notifiable Diseases and Other Conditions of Public Health Importance document for the relevant MMWR year

hl7v251.messageContext: OBR-31 Reason for Study
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
This field should be populated using the standardized vocabulary from PHVS_NotifiableEvent_Disease_Condition_CDC_NNDSS Value Set Code for the conditions listed in the Event Codes tab.

DMB Will fail the message if data is not received in this field.

Refer to the Event Code List of Nationally Notifiable Diseases and Other Conditions of Public Health Importance document for the relevant MMWR year.

This references can be found on the NNDSS Messaging Mapping Guide web site: https://wwwn.cdc.gov/nndss/case-notification/related-documentation.html

elements.name: Arbovirus
elements.description: Type of arbovirus the case was infected with.

hl7v251.messageContext: Observation/OBX Segment with this variable ID and label
hl7v251.implementationNotes: DMB Will fail the message if data is not received in this field.

elements.name: Case Class Status Code
elements.description: Status of the case/event as suspect, probable, confirmed, or "not a case" per CSTE/CDC/ surveillance case definitions.

hl7v251.messageContext: Observation/OBX Segment with this variable ID and label
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
Valid Values:
Confirmed 
Not a Case 
Probable 
Suspect 

Note: 'Unk - Unknown' is not a valid value for the Arboviral System.

If no data is received DMB will fail the message or If receive “Unknown” DMB will fail the message.

elements.name: State Case Identifier
elements.description:
States use this field to link NEDSS investigations back to their own state investigations.
Note:
If a case has been sent via ArboNET, use this same StateID to tie back to the original case.

State Case ID is used as a primary case identifier (i.e. to identify as unique case) and would be used for case counts as well as for making updates to the case that was already sent.

hl7v251.messageContext: Observation/OBX Segment with this variable ID and label
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
DMB will fail the message if data is not received in this field.

If a case has been sent via ArboNET, use this same StateID to tie back to the original case.

elements.name: Mother-Infant Case ID Linkage
elements.description:
Mother and Infant Case ID would be helpful to look in detail about maternal as well as newborn information.

If the case is for mother, please put the related Infant case ID (s) which could include multiple case ID's in case of multiple births.

If the case is for an infant or newborn, please put the Mom's Case ID.

hl7v251.messageContext: Observation/OBX Segment with this variable ID and label

elements.name: Local record ID
elements.description:
Sending system-assigned local ID of the case investigation with which the subject is associated.

Note:
This variable is not used by NNDSS or ArboNET as the primary case identifier and would not be used for identifying unique case / case counts as well as for making updates to the case that was already sent.

hl7v251.messageContext: OBR-3-Filler Order Number
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
<same value in each OBR instance>

where OBR-3.1 is the internally assigned case/investigation ID, OBR-3.3 is the OID for sending application as assigning authority, and OBR-3.4 is the literal value 'ISO'.  The UID and label are not passed in the message.

elements.name: Date First Electronically Submitted

hl7v251.messageContext: OBR-7-Observation Date/time
hl7v251.implementationNotes:
<same value in each OBR instance>

elements.name: Date of Electronic Case Notification to CDC
elements.description:
Date/time this version of the notification was sent.  It will be the same value as NOT103 for the original notification.  For updates, this is the update/send date/time.

Note: This variable is used by NNDSS to identify the most recent case notification message.

hl7v251.messageContext: OBR-22-Result Report/Status Chg Date/time

elements.name: Serum Paired Antibody Test Interpretation
elements.description:
Serum paired antibody result. 

This is an interpretation based upon the lab values paired sera testing of specimen 1 (Acute) and Specimen 2 (Convalescent). For Arboviral lab tests, these tests are usually PRNT.

elements.name: Other Arboviral Disease Transmission Mode
elements.description:
Other Arboviral unusual and rare disease transmission modes.

This variable is used to differentiate the "In Utero (Transplacental)" vs "Perinatal". This variable also can be used to capture more than one transmission mode.

Other valid values such as blood donation, blood transfusion, lab acquired, organ transplant are not included in this value set as they exists as variables in the current guide as risk factors.
